      passage: `<p>Publishing in 2013, a group headed by Oona M. Lönnstedt concluded that ocean acidification bears heavily on the behavior of the fish <em>Pomacentrus amboinensis</em>. Yet that group had worked from a mean sample of just 28 or so fish. Surveying what a range of scientists had concluded about acidification and fish behavior, a 2022 review led by Jeff C. Clements cautioned that so small a sample can widen the door to biased analysis—analysis that, in its turn, can help to produce published reports that overstate how large the true effects really are.</p>`,
